Module 2 – Graded Quiz Study Notes

Core Concepts

Variable Assignment
	•	Use = to assign values
	•	= assigns, == compares

Comparison Operators
	•	==, !=, <, >, <=, >=
	•	Return Boolean values (True / False)
	•	Strings compare alphabetically (ASCII order)

Logical Operators
	•	and: both conditions True
	•	or: at least one condition True
	•	not: reverses Boolean value

⸻

Conditional Statements
	•	if, elif, else
	•	if and elif must end with :
	•	Only one block executes
	•	else has no condition
	•	Indentation is required

Execution order:
	1.	if
	2.	elif (checked only if previous is False)
	3.	else (runs if all above are False)

⸻

Functions
	•	Defined using def
	•	Parameters receive values
	•	return sends value back
	•	print() only displays output

Structure:

def function_name(parameter):
    code
    return value


⸻

Arithmetic Operators
	•	+ - * / basic math
	•	// floor division
	•	% modulo (remainder)

Examples:
	•	7 // 2 = 3
	•	7 % 2 = 1

⸻

Quiz Skill Examples

Nested Function Calls

def product(a, b):
    return a * b

print(product(product(2,4), product(3,5)))

Output: 120

Complex Conditional Example

def get_remainder(x, y):
    if x == 0 or y == 0 or x == y:
        remainder = 0
    else:
        remainder = (x % y) / y
    return remainder

print(get_remainder(10, 3))

Output: 0.3333333333333333

⸻

Best Practices

Self-Documenting Code
	•	Clear variable names
	•	Readable structure
	•	Minimal comments needed

⸻

Common Syntax Errors
	•	Missing :
	•	Incorrect indentation
	•	Misspelled keywords
	•	Mixed or incorrect quotes
	•	Case sensitivity errors
	•	Using = instead of ==
	•	Data type mismatches

⸻

Quiz Tips
	•	Trace code step-by-step
	•	Evaluate inner function calls first
	•	Read conditions left to right
	•	Syntax errors = zero credit

Easy way to remember if / elif / else:
	•	if → “Check this first”
	•	elif → “If not that, check this” (backup choices)
	•	else → “If nothing else worked, do this” (default)

Memory trick: Only the first True wins.
